Reasoning: The paper discusses a web-based annotation system for managing large-scale multilingual Code Switching (CS) data annotation. CS is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is covered by several sub-categories in computer science. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as it specifically deals with NLP. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possibility as it deals with the organization and retrieval of large amounts of data, which is relevant to the management of the annotation data. cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories as they deal with machine learning and data processing, which are important components of the annotation system. Finally, cs.DL (Deep Learning) is a possibility as deep learning is often used in NLP tasks and could be relevant to the system's language-specific data preprocessing tool.
